<br>
All three bodies lay in their wake.  The night echoed inside the tower with the regular noises of the hills again.  Then a sound of movement echoed on the floor inside the tower.  The remaining guard who had been knocked unconscious awoke, groggy.<br>
<br>
He looked over at his partner and could see that life had allready left him.  Closing his eyes he glanced over at Aaeon's body.  He crawled towards her, slowly.  The guard removed his gauntlets from his hands exposing his hands to the brisk cold that haunted the tower.  He got side by side with her and placed his hand over her mouth checking for life.  Seconds seemed like days but a sudden cold breath encased his hand.<br>
<br>
Guard: &quot;Hold on Aaeon.  Just a bit longer.&quot;  He picked himself up into a sitting position and glanced over her body to find her mortal wound.  He placed his hands over her chest clotting the wound with both his hands.  &quot;May your faith in Rodcet Nife heal you.&quot;<br>
<br>
A dim blue aura encased his hands.  Blue strands of magic encased Aaeon and slowly fell inside her body through her wound.<br>
<br>
