<br>
<br>
Zaboxx and Phelsuma appeared out of the portal.  Zaboxx looked around at his surroundings, he yawned.<br>
<br>
Phelsuma: “I take it you need a break from all that destruction you just caused.”<br>
<br>
Zaboxx: “Well, you try killing three paladins and see how peppy you feel.”  Zaboxx scowled at Phelsuma.  He removed his two handed sword from his back and planted it straight into the ground.  He stretched as the burden of the sword was released from his back.  He crouched down and sniffed the air.<br>
<br>
Phelsuma walked over and stood in front of him, “I don’t sense him around us.  When did he say he would meet us.”<br>
<br>
Zaboxx stood back up, “He told me to meet him here at this spot at this time.  We were lucky that those paladins were push overs.”  Zaboxx grinned.<br>
<br>
Phelsuma: “Wait!  I feel something.”<br>
<br>
Zaboxx: “Where is he coming from?”<br>
<br>
A figure appeared in front of the two.  It was dressed in a long black cloak.  The figure’s face was hidden along with the rest of his body.  The cloak seemed to shroud its whole frame giving its whole body a disguise from what its physical frame looks like.  The figure motioned for the two to stand up.  In the sudden appearance of the mysterious figure Zaboxx and Phelsuma fell to the ground and they both kneeled.<br>
<br>
Zaboxx spoke first, “Hello exalted one.  We have served your bidding and killed the paladin known as Aaeon.  Your deception worked.  She gave us her unsuspecting trust and we used it against her.”<br>
<br>
The figure nodded in approval.<br>
<br>
Phelsuma spoke next, “I have found also where the other two are.  Using the powers you have given me I have found the wizard residing back in his home with the Erudites and I also have located the rogue.  She is in Felwithe.<br>
<br>
The figure nodded in approval once more.  Then he spoke, “What of her husband?”<br>
<br>
Zaboxx answered, “It seems that the ranger has eluded us for the time being.  We will find him, I promise you that.”<br>
<br>
The figure hung its head down in disapproval, and removed its arms showing the off color white of its hands.  A spark suddenly appeared and jumped from one hand to the other forming an arc.  Raising its hands, the figure pointed down at Zaboxx and released the ball of electricity.  Zaboxx recoiled back from his knees.  His body lay on the ground with slight spasm’s vibrating his limbs.  A thin stream of smoke smoldered from his chestplate.<br>
<br>
The figure finally spoke, “I did not recruit you two for failure.  You will do as I say.  You will obey my every command and if I hear that you have failed me again, I will not be as lenient towards you.”  The figure walked up towards Phelsuma and cupped her chin with one of the figures free hands.  Phelsuma could feel the heat that had just been discharged.  She looked up and met the eyes of the figure.  “ I pray Phelsuma, that you and this shadowknight find a way to appease me.  It would be a pity to remove you from this planet.”  The figure let go of her face and turned around facing away from them.  The figure removed his hood releasing its long dark black hair.  Turning around, the figure made it known who he was, “Lord Innorrukk does not take failure well.  I expect on our next encounter that you bring better news.”  Lord Innorrukk disappeared in a ball of dark fire.<br>
<br>
Phelsuma breathed hard.  She looked over at Zaboxx who was laying unconscious still.  Looking up at the sky she caught her breath again and stood up.<br>
<br>
